ὖ</foreign>), <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.2783.4</biblScope> </bibl> <date TEIform=\"date\">(iv B. C.)</date>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hellad.</author> </bibl> ap. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4040.tlg001:p.530\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Phot.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Bibl.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">p.530</biblScope> </bibl> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ B.\">B.</a></author> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τό τ᾽ ὖ</foreign> or <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τό θ᾽ ὗ</foreign> might be read in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0309.tlg001:33:3\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Achae.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">33.3</biblScope> </bibl> for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τοῦ ῡ</foreign> codd.<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ath.\">Ath.</a></author> </bibl>; later <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τὸ υ ψιλόν</foreign> or <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τὸ ψιλὸν υ</foreign> (as name of the first letter of <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὕαλος, υἱός,</foreign> etc.), <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Theognost.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Can.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18</biblScope></bibl>, Sch. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg011.perseus-grc1:896\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">896</biblScope></bibl>, Ps. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0087.tlg036:116\" default=